<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-03-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-03-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="775" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d775">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">093.612/52: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-27">March 27,
                                1944</date>.<lb/>[Received March 28—11:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1067. Moscow papers for March 25 announce the award of the Order of
                            Suvorov First Class to General Marshall “for distinguished military
                            activity and services in the direction of the American Armed Forces in
                            the struggle against the common enemy of the Soviet Union and the United
                            States of America, Hitlerite Germany”.<note n="4" xml:id="d775fn1">Moscow newspapers for June 7 reported the presentation ceremony at
                                the Soviet Embassy in Washington on June 5.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>